title: FeeTypeEnum
description: The enumerated values to specify an event that has given rise to a fee.

oneOf.title: Assignment
oneOf.description: A cash flow resulting from the assignment of a contract to a new counterparty.

oneOf.title: CorporateAction
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with a corporate action

oneOf.title: CreditEvent
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with a credit event.

oneOf.title: Increase
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with an increase lifecycle event.

oneOf.title: PartialTermination
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with a partial termination lifecycle event.

oneOf.title: Premium
oneOf.description: Denotes the amount payable by the buyer to the seller for an option. The premium is paid on the specified premium payment date or on each premium payment date if specified.

oneOf.title: Renegotiation
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with a renegotiation lifecycle event.

oneOf.title: Termination
oneOf.description: A cash flow associated with a termination lifecycle event.

oneOf.title: Upfront
oneOf.description: An upfront cashflow associated to the swap to adjust for a difference between the swap price and the current market price.
